    <item>
      <title>Lucky $even Strategy on The Price Is Right</title>
      <link>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/lucky-seven-strategy-on-the-price-is-right/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/lucky-seven-strategy-on-the-price-is-right/</guid>
      <description>&lt;script&gt;&#xD;&#xA;document.addEventListener(&#34;DOMContentLoaded&#34;, function() {&#xD;&#xA;  document.querySelectorAll(&#34;pre code.language-r&#34;).forEach(function(code) {&#xD;&#xA;    var pre = code.parentNode;&#xD;&#xA;    var wrapper = document.createElement(&#34;details&#34;);&#xD;&#xA;    var summary = document.createElement(&#34;summary&#34;);&#xD;&#xA;    summary.textContent = &#34;Show code&#34;;&#xD;&#xA;    summary.style.cursor = &#34;pointer&#34;;&#xD;&#xA;    summary.style.color = &#34;#888&#34;;&#xD;&#xA;    summary.style.fontStyle = &#34;italic&#34;;&#xD;&#xA;    summary.style.marginBottom = &#34;0.5em&#34;;&#xD;&#xA;    wrapper.appendChild(summary);&#xD;&#xA;    pre.parentNode.insertBefore(wrapper, pre);&#xD;&#xA;    wrapper.appendChild(pre);&#xD;&#xA;  });&#xD;&#xA;});&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/script&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This post serves two purposes: it&amp;rsquo;s both an &lt;strong&gt;analysis of the Lucky $even game&lt;/strong&gt; on The Price Is Right and a &lt;strong&gt;tutorial on data analysis in R&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; covering web scraping, data wrangling, visualization, and simulation.  All code is folded by default; click &amp;ldquo;Show code&amp;rdquo; to expand any block and follow along.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Wheel Spin Strategy On The Price Is Right</title>
      <link>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/wheel-spin-strategy-on-the-price-is-right/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 01 Aug 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://www.dustysturner.com/post/wheel-spin-strategy-on-the-price-is-right/</guid>
      <description>&lt;div id=&#34;motivation&#34; class=&#34;section level2&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2&gt;Motivation&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Like many, COVID-19 completely altered our lives as the virus spread across the country and became a mainstay in our society. Though my family and I have been spared of tragedy, we’ve had to find ways to replace kid’s activities, work routines, and social interactions with other (hopefully) enriching activities… Like family games.&lt;/p&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;center&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;img src=&#34;images/cal_beats_reese.jpg&#34; alt=&#34;cal&#34; width=&#34;500&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;figcaption&gt;&#xD;&#xA;Ticket to Ride caused a lot of strife between my kids :)&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/figcaption&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;/center&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;One thing that we’ve added to our new normal is watching &lt;a href=&#34;https://twitter.com/PriceIsRight?s=20&#34;&gt;“The Price is Right”&lt;/a&gt; after dinner. We find it to be a great chance to open up talk of numbers and strategy with our kids.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
